      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s interesting that apparently this is not an expression\n\n```\n@experiment(try)\ntry { true }\n```\n\nThis is an expression, but it doesn\u0027t work:\n\n```\n{x: {try { true }} @experiment(try)}.x\n```\n\nEssentially, I\u0027m trying to convince myself that it\u0027s ok for you to assume there are no experiments. I think it\u0027s ok.",
      "revId": "e0b5f1876f950eaa010225e3a1c1946ffc86f493",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d0cbf29f_56a4fb34",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1038145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-10T10:05:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "```\n{x: {\n\t@experiment(try)\n\ttry {true}\n}}.x\n```\nThat\u0027s a better example, but it still doesn\u0027t work. I guess the only legal places for `@experiment` to appear means it can never be part of an expression.",
      "parentUuid": "86879684_e0407256",
      "revId": "e0b5f1876f950eaa010225e3a1c1946ffc86f493",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
